    <briefdescription>
<para>Mahalanobis distance metric with per-point coordinate uncertainties. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Computes a normalised distance between two points using the per-point sigma values stored in the PointsView. For each dimension the contribution is <computeroutput>(x_i - x_j)^2 / (sigma_i^2 + sigma_j^2)</computeroutput>, which is the correct combination for two independent Gaussian uncertainties.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Requires that sigma values have been set for every dimension via <computeroutput>set_sigma</computeroutput> or <computeroutput>set_sigmas</computeroutput> before clustering.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Ndim</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of dimensions </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TData</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Floating-point type for coordinates and sigma values </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
